threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, SPARC, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The MIPS32 binary is a botnet agent, likely part of a Mirai or Gafgyt variant, designed for IoT device infection. Key indicators include hardcoded SSDP (M-SEARCH) discovery headers for network scanning and a spoofed Windows Google Chrome User-Agent used to mask malicious HTTP traffic. Function analysis reveals manipulation of ELF header constants (0x454c4601) and complex, repetitive obfuscated code structures characteristic of malware droppers and command-and-control agents.
